Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Chapter 3  -  Section 3.6", "Title"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "I",
  StyleBox["n this ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  StyleBox[" notebook, you will explore the behavior of solutions to linear \
differential equations in nonhomogeneous form. The solution arrived at using \
undetermined coefficients will be compared with the computer algebra \
solution.",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  "\n\n",
  StyleBox["In most cases, to adapt this code to other problems, you will \
have to change only the input shown in red. To open a cell grouping, \
double-click on the right-hand side of the double cell marker.",
    FontSize->14]
}], "Subsubtitle"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
  "Problem 23:  y'' - 4y' + 4 y = 2",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(TraditionalForm\`t\^2\)]],
  " + 4t ",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(TraditionalForm\`\[ExponentialE]\^\(2  t\)\)]],
  " + t Sin(2t)"
}], "Section"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Solving the Differential Equation by the Method of Undetermined \
Coefficients\
\>", "Subsection"],

Cell["\<\
We first find the general solution to the homogeneous equation. As we do \
this, we define the left hand side of the equation as lhs[t].\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{\(Clear[y, t]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{\(lhs[y_]\), "=", 
        StyleBox[\(\(y''\)[t] - 4 \( y'\)[t] + 4  y[t]\),
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"Factor", "[", 
      StyleBox[\(r\^2 - 4  r + 4\),
        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "]"}]}], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
Since we have a repeated root, the general solution to the homogeneous \
equation becomes\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{"homsoln", "=", 
      StyleBox[\(\(\[ExponentialE]\^\(2  t\)\) \((C[1]\  + \ C[2]\ t)\)\),
        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}]], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
Taking this solution into account,the trial solution parts for the \
nonhomogeneous equation are as follows. Note that the trial solution for the \
exponential portion was impacted by the solution to the homogeneous equation.\
\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{\(Clear[a, b, c, d, f, g, h, j, k]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{\(y1trial[t_]\), "=", " ", 
        StyleBox[\(a\ t\^2 + b\ t + c\),
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{\(y2trial[t_]\), "=", " ", 
        StyleBox[\(\((d\ t\^3 + f\ t\^2)\)\ \[ExponentialE]\^\(2  t\)\),
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{\(y3trial[t_]\), "=", " ", 
        StyleBox[\(\((g\ t + h)\)\ Sin[2  t]\  + \ \((j\ t + k)\)\ Cos[
                2  t]\),
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ";"}]}], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We will begin by finding the coefficients for the polynomial expression. \
To do this, we will extract the coefficients with the ",
  StyleBox["CoefficientList ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command, which lists coefficients of ",
  StyleBox["t",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  " in order from the constant term to the coefficient of the highest power \
of ",
  StyleBox[" t",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  ". We then set the coefficients on the left side of the equation equal to \
the corresponding coefficients on the right side of the equation and solve \
for a, b, and c."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{"soln1", "=", 
      RowBox[{"Solve", "[", 
        RowBox[{
          RowBox[{\(CoefficientList[lhs[y1trial], t]\), "\[Equal]", 
            RowBox[{"{", 
              StyleBox[\(0, 0, 2\),
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "}"}]}], ",", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            StyleBox[\(a, b, c\),
              FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "}"}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We can use the same technique to solve for the coefficients in the \
exponential expression, except that we need to divide out the exponential \
term before we solve. It is also necessary to remove some of the extra braces \
here with the ",
  StyleBox["Flatten ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  "command."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{"soln2", "=", 
      RowBox[{"Solve", "[", 
        RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"Flatten", "[", 
              RowBox[{"CoefficientList", "[", 
                RowBox[{
                  RowBox[{
                    RowBox[{\(lhs[y2trial]\), 
                      StyleBox["/",
                        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                      StyleBox[\(\[ExponentialE]\^\(2  t\)\),
                        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "//", "Simplify"}], 
                  ",", "t"}], "]"}], "]"}], "\[Equal]", 
            RowBox[{"{", 
              StyleBox[\(0, 4\),
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "}"}]}], ",", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            StyleBox[\(d, f\),
              FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "}"}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "The portion involving the sine and cosine will require a \"by hand\" \
analysis, but ",
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  " will separate out our terms into those not involving ",
  StyleBox["t",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  " and those that are coefficients of ",
  StyleBox["t",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  "."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    \(CoefficientList[lhs[y3trial] // Simplify, t]\)], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
We will set the coefficients of corresponding terms equal to one another and \
solve the resulting system of equations.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{"soln3", "=", 
      RowBox[{"Solve", "[", 
        RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"{", 
            
            StyleBox[\(4  g - 8  h - 4  j \[Equal] 
                0, \(-4\) g - 4  j + 8  k \[Equal] 0, \(-8\) g \[Equal] 0, 
              8  j \[Equal] 1\),
              FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
            StyleBox["}",
              FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], 
          StyleBox[",",
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
          StyleBox[\({g, h, j, k}\),
            FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "]"}]}]], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
Now, we will put these all together to get the general solution.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    \(genlsoln[t_] = 
      homsoln + \((y1trial[t] /. soln1)\) + \((y2trial[t] /. 
            soln2)\) + \((y3trial[t] /. soln3)\)\)], "Input"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Solving the Differential Equation Using the DSolve Command.", \
"Subsection"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We can solve the original differential equation in our computer algebra \
system using the ",
  StyleBox["DSolve",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{"casoln", "=", 
      RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"DSolve", "[", 
          RowBox[{
            RowBox[{\(lhs[y]\), "\[Equal]", 
              
              StyleBox[\(2  t\^2 + 4  t\ \[ExponentialE]\^\(2  t\) + 
                  t\ Sin[2  t]\),
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ",", \(y[t]\), ",", "t"}], 
          "]"}], "//", "Simplify"}]}]], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "Except for a trigonometric identity that was used in the ",
  StyleBox["DSolve",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command, the solutions look identical. We can check this out by asking ",
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  " whether or not they are equal. If they are, it will return True; if not, \
it will return False. Sometimes, ",
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  " cannot determine whether or not they are equal until the expressions are \
simplified."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    \(\((y[t] /. casoln)\) \[Equal] genlsoln[t] // Simplify\)], "Input"]
}, Closed]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
FrontEndVersion->"5.0 for Microsoft Windows",
ScreenRectangle->{{0, 1024}, {0, 685}},
WindowSize->{756, 561},
WindowMargins->{{8, Automatic}, {-160, Automatic}}
]

